snippet.textDisplay:
First of everything,a big big Thank You to the whole Coke Studio team ❤.

Secondly,people who listen to the senseless current Bollywood music,dance to them in their weddings and parties and keep that music in thier playlists come here and all at a sudden starts being judgmental about the ever beautiful music from this platform called "Coke Studio".

I loved all the 3 songs so far and all of them had their own beautiful melodious aura,
Laal Meri Pat made me feel like i am somewhere else,Roney na diya made me flow through a stream of old sad memories and Baazi made me stand and dance to it's sweet melodies.
Tell me people where in the world can you find a place where you can get such splendidly beautiful and uniquely different range and genres of music?

Thirdly,everyone has the choice to be a critic to Coke Studio because of the fact that it's something very public,but being a critic while still being respectful is a thing we all need to learn,respect and adapt because we sit here and type a comment while the people behind this go sleeples for days and nights to create great music for us,the people,being respectful never takes anything from a person i believe.

This is yet another great episode and all the artists need a huge round of applause for their beautiful work.

Zaw Ali is a bliss of fresh air in the music fraternity and i think we have just found another Queen of the music.
Coke Studio,you guys slayed it yet again.
Take a Bow and hats off to you people❤.
